        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 9:10PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 910 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 7 miles south of Sedan to 11 miles west
of San Jon, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Nara Visa, Amistad, Logan, San Jon, Ute Lake State Park, Hayden
and Bard.

This includes Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 339 and 371.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
